++# Owner-Op Road Ready v96.5.0
++
++## Pre-trip rule tied to a real 10-hour reset
++- A new Pre-trip is requested only when the next Driving start follows at least 600 continuous minutes of OFF DUTY and/or SLEEPER BERTH.
++- OFF and SB can be combined when they are continuous.
++- A midnight calendar boundary by itself never creates a new Pre-trip requirement.
++- Continuous Driving split between two log dates remains one Driving period.
++
++## Live Driving guard
++- Direct Driving is blocked after a qualifying 10-hour reset until an ON DUTY Pre-trip event is saved.
++- The status screen switches to ON DUTY / Pre-trip inspection and explains why.
++- The Depart Loaded shortcut uses the same guard.
++- The app does not save or invent Pre-trip time automatically.
++
++## Certification and DOT Check
++- Historical missing Pre-trip records after 10h+ rest are review items instead of automatic time-changing fixes.
++- Accurate logs can be certified with the review shown.
++- The false “Add 15m pre-trip” card is removed from midnight-only cases.
++
++## Preserved behavior
++- Pickup BOL / Shipping # and Going to remain linked to the exact event and route leg.
++- Historical event locations, HOS calculations, manual Driving, signing data, DOT HTML, backup/import, and offline sync are unchanged.
++
++## Verification
++- `verify-pretrip-after-10h-reset-v965.mjs`
++- `verify-midnight-pretrip-continuity-v964.mjs`
++- `verify-route-bol-event-link-v964.mjs`
++- Existing shipping-doc, historical-location, pickup-editor, HOS reset, HOS midnight, and minute-boundary checks.
